		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />It appears to be a stylistic choice by Mr.Tanaka, since the same weirdness shows up in the SNES version, Tetris &amp; Dr.Mario. If you'd like though, the prototype version of the game, named <a href="https://tcrf.net/Proto:Dr._Mario_%28NES%29/PlayChoice-10_Prototype" class="postlink">Virus</a>, contains versions of the jingles that don't end abruptly.<br /><br />Edit: Corrected link. I knew it was one of the protos. <img src="./images/smilies/icon_razz.gif" alt=":P" title="Razz" />

		

		</td>
